"Wirtz P., Fricke R., Biscoito M.J.","The coastal fishes of Madeira Island - New records and an annotated check-list",2008,"Zootaxa",,"1715",,"1","26",,,,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-40649108056&partnerID=40&md5=81a7a21bdc106b637f21ea60ff3d48dd","Centro de Ciências do Mar, Universidade do Algarve, Campus de Gambelas, PT 8005-139 Faro, Portugal; Staatliches Museum für Naturkunde, Rosenstein 1, 70191 Stuttgart, Germany; Museu Municipal do Funchal (Historia Natural), Rua da Mouraria 31, PT 9004-546 Funchal, Madeira, Portugal","Wirtz, P., Centro de Ciências do Mar, Universidade do Algarve, Campus de Gambelas, PT 8005-139 Faro, Portugal; Fricke, R., Staatliches Museum für Naturkunde, Rosenstein 1, 70191 Stuttgart, Germany; Biscoito, M.J., Museu Municipal do Funchal (Historia Natural), Rua da Mouraria 31, PT 9004-546 Funchal, Madeira, Portugal","A check-list of the coastal fishes of Madeira Island is presented. The species Rhincodon typus, Megalops atlanticus, Apterichtus caecus, Apterichtus sp., Chelidonichthys lucernus, Caranx crysos, Lutjanus goreensis, Crystallogobius linearis, and Canthidermis sufflamen are recorded for the first time from Madeira waters. We have recognized 13 previous records as identification errors or registration errors and indicate 14 other records as doubtful. Including the nine new records, we list 226 species from the coastal waters of Madeira Island. Copyright © 2008 Magnolia Press.","Eastern Atlantic; Global warming; Marine biodiversity; Reef fish","Apterichtus; Canthidermis sufflamen; Caranx crysos; Chelidonichthys lucernus; Crystallogobius linearis; Lutjanus goreensis; Megalops atlanticus; Pisces; Rhincodon typus",,,,,,"Almada, F., Almada, V.C., Domingues, V., Brito, A., Santos, R.S., Molecular validation of the specific status of Parablennius sanguinolentus and Parablennius parvicornis (Pisces: Blenniidae) (2005) Scientia Marina, 69 (4), pp. 519-523; Almada, F., Almada, V.C., Guillemaud, T., Wirtz, P., Phylogenetic